<div id="requesting-an-api-access-token" class='section-block'>
    <h4>Requesting an API Access Token</h4>
    <p>
        Before you can send requests to Zube's API endpoints, you will need an access token. To get an access token from Zube, you will need to create a <a href="https://jwt.io/introduction/" target="_blank">JSON Web Token (JWT)</a> signed by your private key and encode it using the <code>RS256</code> algorithm. Zube checks the JWT you create with your private key against the public key stored by Zube and returns a JWT you can use to access Zube's other API endpoints.
    </p>
    <div class='code-block'>
        The following Node.js code can be used to generate the JWT used to request an API access token.
        <pre class='language-javascript'>
            <code class="language-javascript">
                // Generate a JWT with your zube_private_key.pem to send to Zube
                var fs = require('fs');
                var jsonwebtoken = require('jsonwebtoken'); //$ npm install jsonwebtoken

                var client_id = YOUR_CLIENT_ID;
                var private_key = fs.readFileSync(PATH_TO_PEM_FILE);

                var now = Math.floor(Date.now() / 1000);
                var jwt = jsonwebtoken.sign({
                    iat: now,
                    exp: now + 60, // Set expiration to 1 minute because Zube expects your JWT to expire in 10 minutes or less
                    iss: client_id // Set the issuer to your Zube client_id
                }, private_key, { algorithm: 'RS256' });

                console.log(jwt);
            </code>
        </pre>
    </div>
</div>
